cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DS

This paper discusses the use of Normalized Compression Distance (NCD) in clustering and classifying data, specifically in the context of malware classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). 

The paper also discusses the theoretical properties of compression algorithms, which suggests a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

Additionally, the paper proposes variants of NCD to mitigate the problem of classifying large malware files, which could be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
